00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:18,700
In February 1959, nine experienced hikers embarked on an expedition to the Ural Mountains, but their journey ended in a horrific and inexplicable tragedy. The group, led by Igor Dyatlov, consisted of seasoned athletes and outdoor enthusiasts from the Ural Polytechnic Institute.

2
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:35,160
As we count down the most disturbing facts about the Dyatlov Pass Incident, number 9 is the strange behavior of the group before their disappearance. They had been warned about the dangers of the trek, but they seemed to be drawn to the challenge.

3
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:49,080
Number 8 is the discovery of the group's tent, which had been ripped open from the inside. It was as if they had been in such a hurry to escape that they didn't even take the time to properly exit the tent.

4
00:00:49,080 --> 00:01:05,440
Number 7 is the lack of explanation for the hikers' disappearance. There were no signs of a struggle, no footprints leading away from the campsite, and no indication of what could have caused them to flee in such a panic.

5
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:16,700
Number 6 is the strange condition of the hikers' bodies. Some had severe internal injuries, including broken ribs and fractured skulls, while others had no visible injuries at all.

6
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:32,080
Number 5 is the presence of radioactive contamination on some of the hikers' clothing. The source of this radiation is still unknown, but it has been speculated that it could be connected to the strange lights seen in the area.

7
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:45,260
Number 4 is the reports of strange lights and sounds in the area. Several witnesses claimed to have seen glowing orbs and heard unusual noises, which some believe could be connected to the hikers' disappearance.

8
00:01:45,260 --> 00:02:01,500
Number 3 is the bizarre state of the hikers' clothing and gear. Some were found to be wearing only their underwear, while others had no shoes on their feet. It was as if they had been forced to flee in a state of extreme panic.

9
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:12,920
Number 2 is the strange behavior of the Soviet authorities in the aftermath of the incident. They seemed to be more interested in covering up the truth than in investigating the hikers' disappearance.

10
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:26,280
And number 1 is the unexplained phenomenon that has been dubbed the 'Dyatlov Pass anomaly'. It is a strange, unexplained energy field that has been detected in the area, which some believe could be connected to the hikers' disappearance.

11
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:40,960
The Dyatlov Pass Incident remains one of the most bizarre and unexplained events in modern history, and it continues to fascinate and terrify us to this day. As we reflect on the strange circumstances surrounding the hikers' disappearance, we are left with more questions than answers.

